 Port Elizabeth - Police in Kwazakele, Port Elizabeth, have appealed to the public for assistance in tracing the parents of a lost seven-year-old boy from Peddie. "Community members brought in a lost seven-year-old boy at the Kwazakele CSC on Sunday," said police spokesperson, Captain Andre Beetge. "From what could be understood, the child mentioned that he is from Peddie with his parents. "An urgent appeal is made to the community to assist police in finding this boy's parents so he can be reunited with them." Capt Beetge said that the following is information the boy could manage to tell police: "Milisa Nyangwa is dressed in grey and black top, black and grey short, black shoes, short hair and is light in completion," Capt Beetge said. "He does not know the area of Kwazakele at all. "Any person that can assist police in finding his parents can contact the Kwazakele police at 041 408 7744 or 071 609 4078 or 08600 10111." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 